news.headline: Oracle in Talks With Meta for Cloud Computing Deal
news.summary: Oracle is in discussions with Meta Platforms for a cloud computing deal worth about $20 billion. news.headline: Heard on the Street Recap: TikTok Is Saved Again
news.summary: TikTok deal here--but details are scant.  President Trump said he and Chinese leader Xi Jinping reached an agreement for a group of investors to take control of TikTok’s U.S. operations.  A TikTok deal was widely expected, but still sparked some weakness for U.S.-based rivals.

news.headline: Oracle stock surges on potential $20B Meta AI cloud deal
news.summary: Investing.com -- Oracle Corporation (NYSE:ORCL) stock surged 4.4% to a session high heading into the close on Friday after Bloomberg reported the company is in talks with Meta Platforms (NASDAQ:META) for a cloud computing deal worth approximately $20 billion.
